        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 8:06PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 806 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Madras, or near Newnan,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Brooks, Fayetteville, Starrs Mill, Woolsey, Palmetto, Tyrone, Inman,
Peachtree City, Senoia, Cannongate, Jw Smith Reservoir, Sandy Creek,
Lake Horton, Thomas Crossroads, Madras, Newnan, Fairburn, and City of
South Fulton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central and west central Georgia.</instruction>
